                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5112 France/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-27T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 27—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. At his lunch for Lindbergh<note n="3" xml:id="d663fn3">Charles A. Lindbergh
                        arrived in Paris May 21 on nonstop flight from New York.</note> yesterday,
                    Briand told me that he wished in a few days to talk with me about his suggested
                    pact between France and the United States. He said that the reception of the
                    idea was so favorable that it ought to be studied, but that he did not desire to
                    move unless he was in entire agreement with President Coolidge.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
